==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Illiberal
<hw>Il*lib"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>illiberalis</ets>; pref. <ets>il-</ets> not + <ets>liberalis</ets>
liberal: cf. F. <ets>illib⟦eacute⟧ral</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
liberal; not free or generous; close; niggardly; mean; sordid.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A thrifty and <xex>illiberal</xex> hand.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Mason.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating a lack of breeding, culture, and the
like; ignoble; rude; narrow-minded; disingenuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not well authorized or elegant; <as>as,
<ex>illiberal</ex> words in Latin</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Illiberalism</ent>⟦br⟧
